eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 5 Years
Maximum age: 80 Years

Subjects may have received bevacizumab, VEGF-Trap, or other VEGF blocking tyrosine
             kinase inhibitors, provided that they did not progress while receiving one of these
             agents. Subjects may not have previously received pazopanib.
Patients must be in first CR/VGPR

Men who partner with a woman of childbearing potential, unless they agree to use
             effective contraception while on study drug.
Life expectancy of greater than 8 weeks
Serum creatinine within institutional normal limits

groups.description: Patients receive pembrolizumab IV over 30 minutes on day 1. Treatment repeats every 21 days for up to 24 courses in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (pembrolizumab)

outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of dose-limiting toxicities as assessed by the Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events (CTCAE) version 3.0

outcome_measures.analysis_method: To understand how prediction accuracy is influenced by clinical and pathological variables, such as smoking history, histologic subtype (AC vs. SQC), RNA integrity, and tumor cell content, as well as their pairwise interactions, logistic regression model allowing covariate will be used to model sensitivity and specificity. In particular, patients will be divided into true positives and true negatives, namely those remained alive at least 36 months after surgery and those who died within the same period.
outcome_measures.measure: Sensitivity and specificity of prediction model
Percentage of Participants with CR, Determined by the Investigator on the basis of PET and CT Scans
outcome_measures.time_frame: Within 6 to 8 weeks after Day 1 of Cycle 6 (up to approximately 23 weeks) (1 cycle:21days)
